Gold Extends Rally to Record Above $1,900 on Mounting Debt, Economy Risk

-- B y   M i l l i e   M u n s h i
-- 
2011-08-22T19:56:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-22/gold-futures-top-1-900-an-ounce-on-comex-in-new-york-for-the-first-time.html
     Aug. 22 (Bloomberg) --- Gold futures topped $1,900 an ounce
in  New York  for the first time ever. Futures for December
delivery climbed $45.80, or 2.5 percent, to $1,898 an ounce at
3:54 p.m. on the Comex, after touching a record $1,900.80.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
